definition.value: A data item that specifies when an individual is released from the emergency department of a hospital.
An information content entity that describes if an individual does not have a zip/postal code specifying their place of residence.

label.value: initial oxygen saturation information after admission

definition.value: An data item that is the outcome of an oxygen saturation measurement process that takes place no more than 30 minutes after admission to a healthcare provider.
A data item that is the outcome of a temperature measurement process that takes place no more than 30 minutes after admission to a healthcare provider.

label.value: international classification of diseases tenth revision injury diagnosis

definition.value: An information content entity that is about an injury borne by a patient and that has an ICD code as a part.
An information content entity that is the outcome of a person stating how they wish to compensate a due amount.
A postal address that is about a residence a person is living in for a short period of time.
A data item that specifies when a trauma surgeon arrived at the patient's bedside.

label.value: total intensive care unit length of stay data item

definition.value: A data item that provides the cumulative amount of time a patient spent in the ICU during one hospitalization measured in whole day increments.
Each partial or full day must be measured as one calendar day.
A value specification that specifies the situation to which a patient is discharged after hospilaization, including the information that the patient passed away during hospitalization.

A planned process consisting of chest compressions often combined with artificial ventilation, or mouth to mouth in an effort to manually preserve intact brain function until further measures are taken to restore spontaneous blood circulation and breathing in a person who is in cardiac arrest.
A bloodstream infection that is associated with the placing of a central line or an umbilical catheter in an organism.
Central venous access catheter is equivalent to central line
An surgical procedure that was not part of the initial treatment plan.
An admission process through which a patient is admitted to the intensive care unit.

label.value: unplanned intensive care unit admission process

definition.value: An intensive care unit admission process that was not part of the initial treatment plan.
A population of all human beings receiving healthcare from one healthcare provider during a specified time.
The average value (arithmetic mean) of the length of stay data of the patient population of an inpatient healthcare provider.
An information content entity that is about a person that is living in a  country they are not a citizen of without legal immigration or VISA paperwork.
An information content identity that denotes the age of a patient at the time of the specific injury.

A governmental organization that exists within a major administrative subdivision that is occupied by other settlements and governs those settlements while also being governed by their respective major administrative subdivision.
A governmental organization administers a settlement of human beings with defined boundaries.
This term includes cities of any population, not limited to large or urban cities
An information content entity that is about the biological qualities and characteristics most commonly found between the female, male, and intersex categories.

label.value: TMD-approved trauma surgeon backup call schedule

definition.value: A trauma surgeon backup call schedule that has been approved by the trauma medical director.
A physician who has completed an neurosurgery residency program and achieved board certification.
A neurosurgeon role that is the outcome of fullfilling all obligations to be allowed to take a board certification exam in neurosurgery.

A surgeon role borne by a human being and that, if realized, is realized by its bearer using operative manual and instrumental techniques on the nervous system of a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.

label.value: collection of board certified neurosurgeons on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a neurosurgeon role that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification and that are board certified in neurosurgery.

label.value: collection of board eligible neurosurgeons on trauma service

definition.value: A collection of humans that consists only of bearers of a neurosurgeon role that are mentioned in a trauma on call plan specification and that are eligible for board certification in neurosurgery.
A duty holder role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer participating in continuing trauma eduction for an amount of time specified in their program or country.

label.value: coordination of trauma quality improvement and patient safety obligor role

definition.value: A duty holder role that is realized by its bearer organizing and managing a trauma quality improvement and patient safety program.

A duty holder role that inheres in a human being mentioned in an on call plan specification and that, if realized, is realized by its bearer participating a planned process realizing the concretization of the plan specification and being on call exclusively for the organization at specified times that is the contractual partner in the document act that created this role.
A duty holder role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer organizing and overseeing the trauma quality improvement and patient safety program.
A duty holder role that if realized is realized by its bearer evaluating the nursing care provided to trauma patients.
A plan specification that specifies on which schedule and to which extent anesthesia services are provided within a healthcare provider organization.

label.value: work related injury information content entity

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates whether an individual is injured while they are being compensated for their service
An information content identity that describes an individuals method of receiving an income by their contributions of labor or services to society or themselves

label.value: international classification of diseases tenth revision primary external cause code

definition.value: An identifier that denotes the external factor that caused injury or the main reason a patient is admitted to the hospital.

label.value: international classification of diseases tenth revision place of occurrence external cause code

definition.value: An iidentifier that denotes the location of the traumatic injury through a code

label.value: international classification of diseases tenth revision additional external cause code

definition.value: An identifier that denotes one or more external causes in addition to the primary external cause of an injury where necessary using an ICD-10 code.
An object used in order to prevent injury to a child.
An information content entity that indicates whether the safety device that inflates rapidly was utilized during a motor vehicle crash.
An information content entity that reports a patient's injuries assessing nine body regions and scoring injuries on a six point scale.
An identifier specifying the name and version of a software that calculates abbreviated injury scale severity codes.
A data item that denotes the total amount of time a patient has spent on a machine that moves oxygen in and out of their lungs.
A process that leads to intense physical injury to the body.
An information content entity that is about the categorization of an individual's background as it is connected to a geographic region and the shared cultural practices of that region
A pathological process that is the realization of cardiac arrest after hospital arrival and the individual undergoing cardiac arrest receives cardiopulmonary resuscitation.
A bacterial urinary tract infection that is caused when an organism has a catheter in place.
An infection that occurs at a surgical site within a specified period of time.
Inspired by the NCIT definition
A surgical site infection that occurs below the incision made during the procedure in the area of the muscles and the tissues that surround the muscles and occurs within a specified period of time.
